                            <comment id="14551305" author="rohini" created="Tue, 19 May 2015 21:54:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14551474" author="daijy" created="Tue, 19 May 2015 23:42:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to both 0.15 branch and trunk. Thanks Rohini for review!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14555148" author="daijy" created="Thu, 21 May 2015 22:11:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This fix break MR mode. In particular, Pig fails on secure cluster. Need one more fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14555160" author="rohini" created="Thu, 21 May 2015 22:24:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do we need the s3 conf in non local mode? It can be simplified to below.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;JobConf jc;
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.pigContext.getExecType().isLocal()) {
            jc = getExecConf(properties);

            &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Trick to .......
&lt;/span&gt;        } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// If we are running in local mode we dont read the hadoop conf file
&lt;/span&gt;            .........
            properties.setProperty(ALTERNATIVE_FILE_SYSTEM_LOCATION, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;file:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;///&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;
            jc = getLocalConf();
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Pick s3 properties from core-site.xml and add to local conf
&lt;/span&gt;            JobConf s3Jc = getS3Conf();
            ConfigurationUtil.mergeConf(jc, s3Jc);
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14555165" author="thejas" created="Thu, 21 May 2015 22:29:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe s3 is used in non-local modes as well.&lt;br/&gt;
Change looks good to me. (for my reference, since it took me few mins to figure out, the real change is in order in which params are passed to  ConfigurationUtil.mergeConf).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14555170" author="rohini" created="Thu, 21 May 2015 22:32:41 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I believe s3 is used in non-local modes as well.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;   Yes. But the additional code getS3Conf() is only needed in local mode as core-site.xml is not loaded there. Non-local modes load core-site.xml and so will have the s3 properties from that already.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14555172" author="daijy" created="Thu, 21 May 2015 22:34:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Look at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4247&quot; title=&quot;S3 properties are not picked up from core-site.xml in local mode&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-4247&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-4247&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it only need to add s3 properties in local mode, so yes, we can simplify. Attach another patch as Rohini suggested.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14555174" author="rohini" created="Thu, 21 May 2015 22:36:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14555178" author="daijy" created="Thu, 21 May 2015 22:37:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4556&quot; title=&quot;Local mode is broken in some case by PIG-4247&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-4556&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-4556&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-3.patch committed to both 0.15 branch and trunk. Thanks Thejas/Rohini for quick review!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
